GOresults = list(classA=classA.go,classB=classB.go,classC=classC.go,classD=classD.go)

kabs = lapply(GOresults, function(compClass){
  results = list(BP=compClass$BP.result, MF=compClass$MF.result, CC=compClass$CC.result)
  lapply(results, function(section){
    section %>%
    filter(elim < .05) %>%
      filter(Significant >= 10) %>%
             arrange(`Rank in elim`) %>%
             head(15) 
  })
})

for (cls in c('classA', 'classB', 'classC', 'classD')){
  for(sect in c('BP','MF','CC')) {
    kabs[[cls]][[sect]] %>% 
      dplyr::select(-classicFisher) %>%
      dplyr::select(!("Rank in elim")) %>%
      kable( label = cls, caption = sprintf("%s/%s", cls, sect), digits = 2) -> k
      print(k)
      cat('\n\n<!-- -->\n\n') # https://stackoverflow.com/questions/39650166/r-why-kable-doesnt-print-inside-a-for-loop
  }
}

sigmoid = function(z) {1 / (1 + exp(-z))}

dataset = as.data.frame(mcols(gr.promoters))
dataset$enriched = ifelse( dataset$padj < .05, 1, 0)
dataset = dataset %>% dplyr::filter(is.finite(enriched)) %>% arrange(log_chip_signal_mean)

#dataset = dataset[11:(nrow(dataset)-10),]


mod = glm(enriched ~ log_chip_signal_max, data=dataset[11:(nrow(dataset)-10),], family = "binomial")
dataset$prediction = sigmoid(predict(mod,newdata=dataset))

curve = data.frame(
  log_chip_signal_max=seq(
    min(dataset$log_chip_signal_max),
    max(dataset$log_chip_signal_max),
    length.out=50))
curve$y = sigmoid(predict(mod, newdata=curve))


dataset=dataset %>% arrange(log_chip_signal_max)
ggplot(dataset[11:(nrow(dataset)-10),], aes(x=log_chip_signal_max, y=enriched)) +
